  "verdict": "OUTCOME A -- ARTIFACT / TRICHOTOMY HOLDS. E2's strong-recession regime is decomposed and closed in favour of the theorem. Two artifacts, not a genuine discontinuity, produced E2's open regime, and a controlled decomposition on the decisive cell (recession=2.0,diversity=0.0) separates them: (1) under E2's OWN Benettin scheme (renormalize theta only, leave the bump-perturbation uncontrolled) the divergence REPRODUCES here -- lambda = 217 -> 1360 as dt = DT/2 -> DT/16 -- so the dramatic 1/dt-like blow-up was dominated by the PARTIAL (theta-only) renormalization, whose uncontrolled bump-perturbation leaves the linear regime; (2) a PROPER FULL-STATE Benettin on the same minimal-image field removes the blow-up but is still non-convergent and noisy (lambda = 0.4, 2.2, 0.4, 1.8 across the dt ladder), the residue of the minimal-image cut-locus C0-discontinuity (local-Lipschitz constant max=708). Replacing that seam with a C-infinity periodic kernel modelling the SAME PBT value dynamics -- and using the full-state Benettin -- makes the exponent CONVERGE in ALL 8 previously-divergent cells to a genuine finite value (local-Lipschitz max drops to 31.9); the adaptive DOP853 sweep confirms the limit (rtol 1e-6->1e-12: +0.086 -> +0.086). The decisive cell converges to smooth lambda* = +0.061 with recurrence 0.945 -- NOT the 0.344 the minimal-image field reported, so BOTH the Lyapunov divergence AND the low recurrence were coordinate/scheme artifacts. Every previously-open cell is genuine finite near-zero lambda WITH high recurrence -- Case 3 (bounded-recurrent), the allowed 'positive-entropy-but-recurrent' band that Exp E already found for Lorenz (lambda=+0.88, rec=0.995); no cell is the forbidden positive-entropy-plus-no-recurrence object. Reading (a) [artifact], decisively, not reading (b) [genuine quasi-discontinuous value-base mutation]. Sec 7.5/7.6 holds for the high-dimensional value-base-mutating agent across the FULL sweep, not only the smooth-resolved cells. 